---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="The Guild — Prerit Khanna" description="Where the cool people who want to build cool things together find each other.">
  <p class="small"><a href="/">← home</a></p>

  <header>
    <h1>The Guild</h1>
    <p class="lede">A guild hall, not a network.</p>
  </header>

  <hr />

  <article>
    <p>
      This is the part of the site that's openly recruiting. If you're reading
      something here and thinking <em>I could help with that</em>, or <em>I want to
      build something adjacent to this</em>, or <em>let's just talk</em> — that's the
      whole point. The Guild is how cool people who want to make things
      together find each other.
    </p>
    <p>
      It splits three ways:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <a href="/guild/crew-calls/"><strong>Crew Calls</strong></a> — open
        roles on errands in motion. Auto-aggregated from the projects
        themselves; if a project is looking for help, it surfaces here.
      </li>
      <li>
        <a href="/guild/boons/"><strong>Boons</strong></a> — what I offer.
        Things I'll help with, things I know enough to be useful at, things
        I'd happily trade time on.
      </li>
      <li>
        <a href="/guild/conversations/"><strong>Conversations</strong></a> —
        standing invitations to talk about specific things. No agenda
        required; sometimes a conversation is the point.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      The bar to reach out is low. The fastest path is email — <a href="mailto:preritandai@gmail.com">preritandai@gmail.com</a>.
    </p>
  </article>
</Base>

<style>
  .lede {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: var(--type-xl);
    color: var(--muted);
    margin: var(--space-2) 0 0;
  }
</style>
